Every year I give a one-hour lecture introducting LaTeX to mathematics undergraduates and Masters students. After the lecture, I normally host a lab session for students to work through some material. In 2020, there is no physical lab session I&rsquo;m afraid&hellip;
Slides The slides for the talk are, of-course, written in LaTeX using the Beamer package. The source code for the files are available on github.
Lab material I&rsquo;ve written a short template file for students to adopt when writing their own reports.
